docs.abstract: In a major war powers decision, an appeals court has blocked the government from forcibly transferring an American detainee to another country.
docs.snippet: In a major war powers decision, an appeals court has blocked the government from forcibly transferring an American detainee to another country.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States cannot forcibly transfer an American citizen being held in Iraq as an Islamic State suspect to the custody of another country without first proving that he is an enemy combatant, a federal appeals court has ruled.

headline.main: Appeals Court Bars U.S. From Transferring American ISIS Suspect
headline.print_headline: U.S. Barred From Moving ISIS Suspect, An American

docs.abstract: Many aid programs would be shunted into a giant new department, where they would be easier to cut or contain, and the Education and Labor Departments could merge.
docs.snippet: Many aid programs would be shunted into a giant new department, where they would be easier to cut or contain, and the Education and Labor Departments could merge.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump plans to propose a reorganization of the federal government as early as Thursday that includes a possible merger of the Education and Labor Departments, coupled with a reshuffling of other domestic agencies to make them easier to cut or revamp, according to administration officials briefed on the proposal.

headline.main: Trump to Propose Government Reorganization, Targeting Safety Net Programs
headline.print_headline: Reorganization Focused on the Safety Net

docs.abstract: Tony Tooke “has determined that it is best for the Forest Service, its future and its employees that he step aside,” Sonny Perdue, the agriculture secretary, said in a statement on Wednesday.
docs.snippet: Tony Tooke “has determined that it is best for the Forest Service, its future and its employees that he step aside,” Sonny Perdue, the agriculture secretary, said in a statement on Wednesday.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The head of the United States Forest Service stepped down Wednesday amid an investigation into sexual harassment accusations against him, a spokesman for the Agriculture Department said.

headline.main: U.S. Forest Service Chief Resigns Amid Sexual Harassment Accusations

docs.abstract: Saying “enough is enough,” Michael D. Cohen filed the defamation suit after denying for the past year that he played any part in a conspiracy to help elect President Trump.
docs.snippet: Saying “enough is enough,” Michael D. Cohen filed the defamation suit after denying for the past year that he played any part in a conspiracy to help elect President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s longtime lawyer, Michael D. Cohen, filed a defamation lawsuit on Tuesday in federal court against Fusion GPS, the firm behind a salacious and largely unsubstantiated dossier that purported to lay out how Russia had aided the Trump campaign. The dossier portrayed Mr. Cohen as a central figure in what it described as a conspiracy.

headline.main: Trump’s Longtime Lawyer Sues BuzzFeed and the Firm Behind Russia Dossier
headline.print_headline: Trump Lawyer Files Defamation Suit Against Dossier Firm

docs.abstract: The Fed is likely to get a new chairman next month, but there are still two job openings just below that post. President Trump controls one. Opponents see the other as an opportunity.

headline.main: Two Federal Reserve Openings Provide One Chance to Counter Trump
headline.print_headline: With 2 Openings at the Fed, A Chance to Counter Trump

docs.abstract: Partisans and analysts are compiling data on how companies are spending their tax savings, in order to score political points and bend corporate behavior.
docs.snippet: Partisans and analysts are compiling data on how companies are spending their tax savings, in order to score political points and bend corporate behavior.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The new Republican tax cut is providing a powerful weapon for the law’s supporters and detractors, as well as investors and analysts, who are mining data on how companies are spending their windfalls in a battle to sway the behavior of voters and executives alike.

headline.main: Spreadsheets at Dawn: The New Tax Battle Is All About Data
headline.print_headline: As Tax Cut Data Trickles In, Partisans Press for a Political Advantage

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s nomination of Gina Haspel to lead the C.I.A. has revived debate over the agency’s post-Sept. 11 interrogation program and still-murky questions about her involvement. Now, on the eve of her Senate confirmation hearing, a striking voice is trying to join that fray: Khalid Shaikh Mohammed.

headline.main: 9/11 Planner, Tortured by C.I.A., Asks to Tell Senators About Gina Haspel
headline.print_headline: 9/11 Planner Asks to Join Fray Over Pick for C.I.A.
